I&#39;m trying to read data from pubsub and use outputWithTimestamp to switch time domains.  However, the watermark doesn&#39;t adjust to use the new time domain.  Two use cases come to mind:

 - Data has been sitting in pubsub subscription for days. I want to switch to assigning windows based on processing time.  However the watermark is days behind the processing time, so window triggers will fire days late.
 - Timestamped data has been sitting in an external source for days, and then gets published to pubsub in a large batch.  I want to switch to assigning windows based on the intrinsic data timestamp which is days behind the published timestamp, without it being considered late data.  Adjusting allowed lateness or allowedTimestampSkew may prevent the data being dropped, but the watermark still advances based on the published timestamp (which advances too slowly because it was published quickly in one large batch).

Any way to make the watermark start over and recompute itself from a certain point in the pipeline, rather than being fixed on the source timestamps?

